divs: Sighting DetailsFirst, this may not be a "UFO", and nothing was seen, only heard. Because there was an incident in nearby in Kokomo, Indiana last month, I thought I should report. I was in my house when I heard a jet going over - this happens infrequently in my area. The sound of the jet was very loud; it was loud enough that I began to think the jet was going to crash somewhere near my house. About 30 to 45 seconds had passed since I first notice the sound, when I decided to go outside and look for the jet or it's path (jet-trail). When I went ouside, (it's a bright sunny day with a few bright clouds in the sky - very nice day), I could still hear the sound of the jet, but could not see it or any trail. The sound eventually faded and I thought that whatever it was, it must have been heading East or Northeast, as the sound diminished in that direction.
Summary: sound only, loud long lasting sonic boom, no visible aircraft
